## Bugs Fixed for Render Deployment

| # | Bug | Fix |
|---|-----|-----|
| 1 | `vite.config.ts` was missing — build would fail | Added `frontend/vite.config.ts` |
| 2 | Frontend served on port 5173, Render expects `$PORT` | Updated Dockerfile to use `$PORT` (10000) |
| 3 | AI service used hardcoded port 8001, not `$PORT` | Updated Dockerfile CMD to use `${PORT:-8001}` |
| 4 | Spring Boot didn't read Render's `$PORT` | Added `${PORT:8080}` to `application.yml` |
| 5 | No SPA fallback — React Router 404s on page refresh | Added `_redirects` file in build stage |
| 6 | No `render.yaml` — manual setup required | Created complete blueprint file |
| 7 | `VITE_API_BASE` baked in at Docker build time | Passed as `buildArgs` in render.yaml |
| 8 | `AI_BASE_URL` hardcoded to localhost | Now set via `render.yaml` env var |

