## Manual Deploy (Without Blueprint)

If you prefer to create services one by one in the Render dashboard:

### Service 1: futureos-ai
- Type: Web Service
- Runtime: Docker
- Dockerfile path: `./ai-service/Dockerfile`
- Docker Context: `./ai-service`
- Env vars: `GROQ_API_KEY`, `AI_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile`

### Service 2: futureos-backend
- Type: Web Service  
- Runtime: Docker
- Dockerfile path: `./backend/Dockerfile`
- Docker Context: `./backend`
- Env vars:
  - `DB_URL` = your Render MySQL JDBC URL
  - `DB_USERNAME` = futureos
  - `DB_PASSWORD` = (from Render MySQL dashboard)
  - `JWT_SECRET` = (generate a random 64-char string)
  - `AI_BASE_URL` = https://futureos-ai.onrender.com

### Service 3: futureos-frontend
- Type: Web Service
- Runtime: Docker
- Dockerfile path: `./frontend/Dockerfile`
- Docker Context: `./frontend`
- Build Arg: `VITE_API_BASE=https://futureos-backend.onrender.com/api`

### Database: futureos-mysql
- Type: MySQL (managed)
- Name: futureos-mysql
- Plan: Free
